{
  "version": 2,
  "buildCommand": "npm run build",
  "outputDirectory": "build",
  "rewrites": [
    {
      "source": "/api/:path*",
      "destination": "/api/:path*"
    }
  ]
}
```

That's it! Much simpler now.

## Explanation:

- **`buildCommand`**: Tells Vercel to run `npm run build` to build your React app
- **`outputDirectory`**: Tells Vercel where the built files are (Create React App outputs to `build/`)
- **`rewrites`**: Routes `/api/*` requests to your serverless functions in the `api/` folder

## Your Project Structure Should Be:
```
your-project/
├── api/
│   └── chat.js              # Serverless function
├── src/                     # React source code
│   ├── App.js
│   ├── index.js
│   └── ...
├── public/
│   ├── index.html
│   └── ...
├── package.json             # Root package.json with React scripts
├── vercel.json              # Updated config
└── .gitignore